definition: The name of the originating data set from which the record was derived.
The verbatim location ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the monitoring program.
The type of site selection used according to the program.
NAdefinition: Site selection not known or reported by the program.

definition: The name of the water body in which the Location occurs.
NAdefinition: Water body name not reported in the original dataset.

definition: The verbatim event ID from the originating source dataset assigned by the program.
noteAndConventions: from source datasets converted to string. Reference to source datasets unique identifier for location data.

definition: The calendar date during which an Event occurred.
NAdefinition: Source data from AREMP do not contain month or day, so no there is no eventDate for those entries.

definition: Categorical description of flow for the reach.
NAdefinition: Description of the flow was not included or reported in the source dataset.
noteAndConventions: Assigned Categories: Flow Whole Reach; Partial Flow or Stagnant Pools; No Flow Dry

definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing information about the Monitoring Programs originating source datasets. This table corresponds to the Record table in the database (.accdb) file.
A unique identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
The acronym of the name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project, from which the source data originates from.
The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.
The name assigned by the Institution (project leader or principal investigator) to the project from which the source data originates from.
The names of, references to, or descriptions of the methods or protocols used during an Event.
URL identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived. The source location for the originating source data or program website.
A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.
NAdefinition: There is no formal citation for this dataset.

definition: URL identifier for the metadata for the originating source dataset or note how to access metadata.
URL identifier for access to the code used to pre-process (download, standardize and tidy) the data sets before integration into the destination dataset.
NAdefinition: Pre-processing code was not used for this dataset.

definition: Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing location data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the Location table in the database (.accdb) file.
A unique numeric identifier assigned to the originating source data's program.
An identifier for the set of location information. Global unique identifier.
The geographic latitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location in decimal degrees.
The geographic longitude (WGS84) of the geographic center of a location in decimal degrees.
Comments or notes about the Location. The location along the reach where geographic coordinates were obtained.
Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing Event data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the Event table in the database (.accdb) file.
Unique global identifier assigned to the location where the event occurred.
An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). Global unique identifier.
Categorical description of beaver impact on the flow of the reach.
NAdefinition: Beaver impacts were not reported in the source data.
noteAndConventions: Assigned categories: Major; Minor; None; NA

definition: The four-digit year in which the Event occurred, according to the Common Era Calendar.
Comma Separated Value (CSV) file containing MeasurementorFact data for the Integrated Stream Habitat Data. This table corresponds to the MeasurementorFact table in the database (.accdb) file.
An identifier for the set of information associated with an Event (something that occurs at a place and time). Global unique identifier.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementValue.
The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
Unique identifier assigned to the measurementType.
The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
